<center>
<h2>Judith Maxwell's Speeches, Presentations <BR>and Publications</h2>
</center>
<p>
"Tranformations in Governance", Presentation to the International Institute on Social Policy, August 27, Queen's University, Kingston. <P>

Presentation to the Labour Market Resource Forum, June 18-19, Ottawa. <P>

"Reconnecting Communities", Presentation to the Annual Meeting of the Community Foundations of Ottawa-Carelton, June 12, Ottawa <P>

Presentation on "Social Union", to Queen's University's Program for Public Executives, June 10, Kingston. <P>

Presentation Concerning Bill C-12: <EM>An Act Respecting Employment Insurance in Canada</EM>, for the Senate Committee on Social Affairs, Science and Technology, June 3, Ottawa. <P>

"Reconnecting Communities", Presentation to the National Conference of the Community Foundations of Canada, May 24, London. <P>

Presentation to Citizenship and Immigration Canada Planning Conference, May 15, Aylmer. <P>

"La réinvention du système de redistribution", Congrès annuel de l'ASDEQ, May 9, 1996, Aylmer.<p>

"<a href="flddrms.htm">Field of Dreams for Canada</a>", Council for Canadian Unity AGM, April 26, 1996, Ottawa.<p>

"<a href="hardtime.htm">Creating Hope in Hard Times</a>", Canadian Club of Ottawa, April 16, 1996.<p>

"Pay for Performance in Canadian Universities", Annual Meeting of AUCC, March 6, 1996, Ottawa.<P>

"Social Dimensions of Economic Growth", Industry Canada Seminar, Feb 9, 1996, Ottawa.<p>

"<a href="socldfeg.htm">Social Dimensions of Economic Growth</a>", 1996 E.J. Hanson Memorial Lecture, Jan 25, 1996, Edmonton.<p>

"<a href="prez2.htm">A Message from the President</a>" in CPRN Annual Report, 1995.<p>

"Public-Private Partnerships in Health Services:  The Socio-Economic Background."  Presentation to conference sponsored by The Canadian Council for Public-Private Partnerships and The Canadian Institute, November 20, 1995, Toronto<p>

<a href="ont-hosp.htm">"Sustainable Health Care of Canada:  Lessons for Ontario."</a>  Presentation to the OHA Convention and Exhibition, November 7, 1995, Toronto <p>

"Balancing our Social Deficit."  Presentation to the Ontario Family Studies/Home Economics Educators" Association, November 3, 1995, Mississauga<p>

"Towards the 21st Century" presentation to Federation of Canada Demographers' Symposium, October 23, 1995, Ottawa.<p>

Social Transformation of the 90's, Synod of the Anglican Diocese of Ottawa, October 20, 1995, Ottawa.<p>

"Evolution of Conditional Grants in Canada:  The Socio-Economic Background."  Presentation to Workshop on Intergovernmental Fiscal Arrangement and Relationships in Canada for delegation from South Africa/IOG, October 18, 1995, Ottawa<p>

<a href="shepherd.htm">"The Social Transformation of the 90s:  Jobs? or Pieces of Work?"</a>  
(Preparing for the 21st Century Lecture Series) Shepherds of Good Hope, September 28, 1995, Ottawa<p>

"A New Social Role for the Corporate Sector", Business Council on National Issues Roundtable on Social Policy Reform, September 5, 1995, Toronto<p>

"Public Sector Issues in the Year 2000."  Agriculture and Agri-Foods Canada Management Retreat, August 28, 1995, Gananoque<p>

"Sustainable Health Care for Canada:  Implications for the Research Agenda."  Canadian Health Economics Research Association, August 24, 1995, Waterloo<p>

