them to us we were ableto eat them.</P><P>I remember that my brother and I would always get the ones that werefilled with custard. My grandfather always got jelly doughnuts for my fatherand himself. My mother and grandmother always had cinnamon sweet rolls.</P><P>I will always remember the first taste of the sweet roll. The custardfilling was so mouth watering. It tasted like the homemade custard in mymom's eclair cake. The chocolate tasted like frosting off of a freshly bakedchocolate cake. The sweet roll its self tasted homemade every time. Thereason I remember all of this so clearly is because my grandfather is theone person I always admired the most in my life.</TD></TR></TABLE></P><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="5" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%"><TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP"><TD WIDTH="30%"><IMG SRC="../images/blank.gif" WIDTH="150" HEIGHT="1" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR><B>By Brittany<BR></B>Grade 5<BR>Herndon, VA</TD><TD WIDTH="68%">If a horse went into a pasture and played what would he do? Where wouldhe go?<BR><BR>If I was a horse in a pasture and was playing I would run a round and kickin the luscious green grass that sparkles like diamonds in the morning frost.I would drink from a sparkling stream that trickles down the glisteningstones and run through the forest around the glistening sun rays that shinedown on the soft soil.</TD></TR></TABLE></P><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P><P><TABLE WIDTH="542" HEIGHT="83" BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING="0"><TR><TD WIDTH="32%" HEIGHT="21"><B>By Jason</B><BR>Grade 10<BR>East Sparta, OH</TD><TD WIDTH="68%"><P>Dirtbike riding is lots of fun but only if it decides to run. </P><P>Now it's started so stop your loafin and ride like me with your throttlewide open.</P><P>I'd say the hardest is in the mud so watch me - the YZ stud.</TD></TR></TABLE></P><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="5" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%"><TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP"><TD WIDTH="31%"><IMG SRC="../images/blank.gif" WIDTH="150" HEIGHT="1" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR><B>By Joi<BR></B>Grade 5<BR>Herndon, VA</TD><TD WIDTH="69%">I am 11 years old.<BR>I am a person who likes to draw.<BR>I am a person who likes football.<BR>I am a person who doesn&ordm;t wake up in the morning.<BR>I am a person who likes jazz.<BR>I am a girl.<BR>I am a person who likes all kinds of foods.<BR>I am a person who likes to dress in fancy clothes.<BR>I am a person who likes dogs, cats, and seagulls.<BR>I am a student.<BR>I am the &quot;future!&quot;</TD></TR></TABLE></P><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT></P><P><TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="5" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" HEIGHT="134"><TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP"><TD WIDTH="32%" HEIGHT="123"><IMG SRC="../images/blank.gif" WIDTH="150" HEIGHT="1" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"ALIGN="BOTTOM"><BR><B>By Jason<BR></B>Grade 5<BR>Arlington, VA</TD><TD WIDTH="68%">I am Jason.<BR>I am a basketball player.<BR>I am a baseball player.<BR>I am a P.E. person.<BR>I am faster than anyone in my class.<BR>I am a person who is a good artist.<BR>I am a person who likes chocolate.<BR>I am student.<BR>I am the future.</TD></TR></TABLE><HR ALIGN=LEFT> <TABLE WIDTH="580" BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="2" CELLPADDING="0" HEIGHT="22"><TR><TD WIDTH="31%" HEIGHT="16"><B>By Saul&nbsp;</B><BR>Grade 5<BR>Arlington, VA</TD><TD WIDTH="69%">I am good at setting goals.<BR>I am a good student.<BR>I am a good artist.<BR>I am someone who likes music.<BR>I am a good singer.<BR>I am a good runner.<BR>I am a good explorer.<BR>I am a good basketball and football player.<BR>I am a good reader.<BR>I am a good speller.<BR>I am a good writer.<BR>I am a student.<BR>I am the future.</TD></TR></TABLE></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><HR><BR><BR><FONT FACE="arial,helvetica"></FONT><BR><B><A HREF="kidzone.html">Click here to return to the Kid Zone</A> </B></P><P ALIGN=CENTER>&