ium</A></B>  hosted by his foundation.<BR>  <BR>    <LI><A HREF="../ld_store/LD-Store.html#anchor99929"><B>Every Child is Learning</B></A>  - <B>The National Center for Learning Disabilities</B>' new project is  designed to help parents, teachers, and early care providers recognize  early warning signs for language and learning disabilities.<BR>  <BR>    <LI><A HREF="../ld_indepth/reading/ltr-cec/ltr1-cec.html"><B>Learning to  Read - Reading to Learn: Helping Children With Learning Disabilities to  Succeed</B></A> - This new public awareness campaign sponsored by the National  Center to Improve the Tools of Educators and twenty-five partner organizations  seeks to minimize the number of students who fail to &quot;learn to read&quot;  during the critical first three years of schooling.<BR>  </UL><H2><IMG SRC="../images/violet.gif" WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="16" ALIGN="BOTTOM"NATURALSIZEFLAG="3"><FONT COLOR="#000000">November 1996<BR></FONT></H2><UL>  <LI><B>NIH Research Chief, G. Reid Lyon,</B> reports on <B><A HREF="../ld_indepth/reading/why_johnny_cant_decode.html">NIH  reading research</A></B> and the promise it offers for children.<BR>  <BR>    <LI><B>LD OnLine Exclusive!</B> Technology expert and adult dsylexic <B>Richard  Wanderman</B> tells <B><A HREF="../ld_indepth/technology/poor_richard_article.html">How  Computers Change the Writing Process for People with Learning Disabilities.<BR>  <BR>  </A></B>  <LI><B>WETA</B> tapes new <B><A HREF="courage_to_soar.html">TV Program  on Learning Disabilities</A></B> featuring <B>Dr. Robert Brooks</B>, nationally-known  LD expert and psychologist.<BR>  <BR>    <LI><A HREF="lab_school_awards.html"><B>The Lab School of Washington</B></A>  celebrates 30 years of helping children with learning disabilities and  honors distinguished Americans <B>James Earl Jones, Dan O'Brien,<BR>  Robert Nixon and Nell Minow</B>. Hear comments from Lab School founder  and director,<B> Sally Smith</B>.<BR>  <BR>    <LI><B>LD OnLine Exclusive! <A HREF="../ld_indepth/teaching_techniques/understanding_textbooks.html">Improving  Students' Understanding Of Textbook Content</A></B> offers special and  general educators a new set of practices to help students with reading  disabilities understand textbooks. Contributed by <B>Barbara Flanagan,  M.S.</B>, Virginia Polytecnic Institute and State University.<BR>  <BR>    <LI><A HREF="../ld_indepth/teaching_techniques/study_skill_instruction.html"><B>A  Call for More Study Skills Instruction</B></A> - <B>Joan Sedita, M.Ed.</B>,  Director of the Landmark Outreach Training Project, explains why LD students  need study skills instruction and offers examples from the L.S.S. model.<BR>  <BR>    <LI><A HREF="nichd.html"><B>The National Institute of Child Health and  Human Development (NICHD</B>)</A> of the National Institutes of Health  (NIH) established a new branch to further the study of learning disabilities  and developmental psychology.<BR>  </UL><H2><IMG SRC="../images/violet.gif" WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="16" ALIGN="BOTTOM"NATURALSIZEFLAG="3">December 1996</H2><UL>  <LI><A HREF="../ld_indepth/technology/hoovers_selection.html"><B>A Selection  of Software for Children with Learning Disabilites</B></A>, compiled by  <B>Anne Hoover</B>, Director of Tutoring Services at the <B>Kingsbury Center</B>  in Washington, D.C. <BR>    <LI>Does special education cost too much? <B><A HREF="cec_time.html">The  Council for Exceptional Children's President, Gerald Hime, responds to  TIME Magazine article.</A></B><BR>    <LI><A HREF="../ld_indepth/general_info/early_childhood_inter.html"><B>Early  Childhood Intervention</B></A> - <B>LDA</B>'s newest pamphlet - offers  information on preschoolers at risk for learning disabilities.<BR>    <LI><B>&quot;<A HREF="../whats_new/christmas_lesson.html">The Christmas  Lesson</A>&quot;</B> a story of love, of giving and of family from <B>Richard  D. Lavoie.</B></UL><P ALIG