<HTML><HEAD>  <META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Adobe PageMill 2.0 Mac">  <TITLE>Reading</TITLE></HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR="#ffffff"><P><!- Page designed and coded by Gene Cowan> <!-MENU Bar Starts Here> <AHREF="../../index.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/main.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="75" HEIGHT="43" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Main Menu" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A> <TABLE BORDER="0" CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0"><TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP"><TD><A HREF="../../whats_new/new.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/new.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="What's New"NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="../../abcs_info/articles-info.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/abc.gif"ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="ABCs" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="../../ld_indepth/resource-guide.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/indepth.gif"ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="In-Depth" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="../../finding_help/help.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/help.gif"ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Getting Help" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="../../ld_calendar/ld-calendar.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/calendar.gif"ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Calendar" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD></TR><TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP"><TD><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="3" HSPACE="0"VSPACE="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></TD><TD><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="3" HSPACE="0"VSPACE="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></TD><TD><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="3" HSPACE="0"VSPACE="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></TD><TD><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="3" HSPACE="0"VSPACE="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></TD><TD><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="3" HSPACE="0"VSPACE="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></TD></TR><TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP"><TD><A HREF="../../audio_clips/audio-clips.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/audio.gif"ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Audio Clips" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="http://www.capaccess.org/cgi-bin/ldonline/netforum/ldf/a/1"><IMG SRC="../../images/bulletin.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0"VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Bulletin Board" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="../../ld_store/LD-Store.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/store.gif"ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="LD Store" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="http://www.weta.capaccess.org/ldonline/ld_survey.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/talk.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Talk Back" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="../../kidzone/kidzone.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/kid.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Kid Zone"NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><!-MENU Bar Ends Here> <BR><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="540" HEIGHT="3" VSPACE="0"NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></P><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Reading</H2><P>Here we take an in-depth look at <B>dyslexia</B>, a learning disabilitythat is associated with reading difficulty. As the most prevalent of alllearning disabilities, dyslexia has received much attention and researchin the past decade, resulting in new information and understanding of readingdisorders and offering great promise for the future.</P><H3>For Starters:</H3><MENU>  <P><A HREF="why_johnny_cant_decode.html"><B>Why Johnny Can't Decode</B></A><B>,  Washington Post, Oct. 27, 1996 </B>- NIH Research chief, G. Reid Lyon,  reports on findings of reading research being conducted at the NIH's National  Institute of Child Health and Human Development.<BR>  <BR>  <B><A HREF="from_letters_to_sounds.html">From Letters to Sounds</A>, Washington  Post, Oct. 27, 1996 </B>- G. Reid Lyon relates the all-to-frequent scenario  of a child who is failing to learn to read in school.<BR>  <BR>  <B><A HREF="ltr-cec/ltr1-cec.html">Learning to Read...Reading to Learn</A>,  Helping Children With Learning Disabilities To Succeed, The National Center  to Improve the Tools of Educators, 1996 </B>- An information kit containing  principles for learning to read; tips for parents and teachers; researcher  as resources and more, based on a synthesis of validated and recognized  research on teaching reading to children with learning disabilities. <BR>  <BR>  <B><A HREF="reading-2.html">Reading and Learning Disabilities</A>, NICHCY  Briefing Paper, National Information Center for Children and Youth with  Disabilities, 1995 - </B>This paper includes a look at learning disabilities  in children and youth, suggestions for parents on how to help their school-age  children learn, and considerations for adults with reading and learning  problems, including a description of the diagnostic process for adults.<BR>  <BR>  <B><A HREF="reading-4.html">Finding the Answer: Dyslexia</A>, Orton Dyslexia  Society Pamphlet, Orton Dyslexia Society, 1996 - </B>This short article  gives general information about the reading disorder known as Dyslexia.  It gives a detailed list of the characteristics that is useful to anyone  who wants to know more about dyslexia.<BR>  <BR>  <B><A HREF="eric540.html">Beginning Reading And Phonological Awareness  For Students With Learning Disabilities</A>, ERIC Digest #E540, 1995 </B>-  This short digest describes the importance of phonological awareness in  the process of learning to read. A companion digest for teachers is available  in the Teaching Techniques section of LD In-Depth.</MENU><H3>Student Support:</H3><MENU>  <P><B>Learning Through Listening: An Informational Guide for Students with  Learning Disabilities, Recording for the Blind &amp; Dyslexic</B> - Learn  how recorded books can help you reach your educational and career goals.  Order this FREE guide from RFB&amp;D at Ph. 1-800-221-4792. A companion  guide for educators and parents is also available.</MENU><H3>Parent Resources:</H3><MENU>  <P><B>Bridges to Reading: What to Do When You Suspect Your Child Has A  Reading Problem: A Kit of First-Step Strategies, Parents' Educational Resource  Center, 1995 -</B> A comprehensive kit full of step-by-step strategies  to identify, understand and address your child's reading problem. It contains  eight strategy based booklets, two audio tapes, reference guides, activity  booklet and much more -- all written in simple, easy to read language.  Order from PERC at 1-800-471-9545.</MENU><H3>Learn more about it:</H3><MENU>  <P><A HREF="../../finding_help/publications_help/dyslexia_pubs.html"><B>Our  selection of publications</B></A> will guide you to more in-depth learning.</MENU><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT SIZE="3" WIDTH="540%" NOSHADE><BR></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=-2>&copy;1996 WETA</FONT></BODY></HTML>
