acts about dsycalculia in language that is easy to understand.</MENU><H3>In the Classroom:</H3><MENU>  <P><B>Teaching Math to Students with Learning Disabilities, Parts I and  II, Council for Learning Disabilities, 1996 - </B>Part of the CLD Monograph  Series :Translating Research Into Practice (TRIP), these monographs provide  a wealth of practical ideas and information on teaching math to students  with learning disabilities. Available from CLD, P.O. Box 40303, Overland  Park, KS 66204. Ph. 913/492-8755 Fax 913/492-2546</MENU><H3>Learn more about it:</H3><MENU>  <P><A HREF="../../finding_help/publications_help/math_pubs.html"><B>Our  selection of Mathematics publications</B></A> offers a wealth of resources  for more in-depth learning.<BR>  </MENU><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT SIZE="3" WIDTH="540%" NOSHADE><BR></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=-2>&copy;1996 WETA</FONT></BODY></HTML>
