</B>  <P><B><A HREF="bestadvocates.html">Parents - Children's Best Advocates</A>,  Arlene Mark, Their World 1990, National Center for Learning Disabilities  - </B>An empowering article on the importance of the unique knowledge only  a parent has! <BR>  <BR>  <B><A HREF="doctors.html">A Parent's Guide to Doctor's, Disabilities, and  the Family</A>, NICHCY, 1990- </B>A complete guide to choosing a primary  health care provider or pediatrician for the child with special needs.<BR>  <BR>  <B><A HREF="parent_observations.html">Parent Observation Profile</A>, Understanding  Learning Disabilities: A Parent Guide and Workbook, Learning Disabilities  Council, 1991- </B>This form provides a useful tool for parents to share  information about their child with school personnel and service providers.<B>  <BR>  <A HREF="parentsrights.html"><BR>  Parent's Rights</A>, Understanding Learning Disabilities: A Parent Guide  and Workbook, Learning Disabilities Council, 1991-</B> An easy-to-understand  guide to parent's rights under Public Law 94-142 and 101-476, The Individuals  with Disabilities Education Act (IDEA) <BR>  <B><A HREF="letter_writing.html"><BR>  Communicating Through Letter Writing</A>, NICHCY publication PA9 - </B>A  complete guide to communicating with school personnel regarding a child  suspected of having a learning disability. Also explains the special education  process.<BR>  <BR>  <B><A HREF="preventburnout.html">Preventing Parent Burn Ou</A><A HREF=  "parentburnout.html">t</A>, Sherry R. Latson, LDA Newsbriefs, Jan./Feb.1995  - </B>An in-depth look at the coping strategies needed to parent a child  with learning disabilities. A &quot;must-read&quot; for every parent!</MENU><H3>Learn more about it:</H3><MENU>  <P><A HREF="../../finding_help/publications_help/parenting_pubs.html"><B>Our  selection of publications</B></A> on parenting offers a wealth of resources  for more in-depth learning.<BR>  </MENU><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT SIZE="3" WIDTH="540%" NOSHADE><BR></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=-2>&copy;1996 WETA</FONT></BODY></HTML>
