VSPACE=0 NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"><P>
<H2><CENTER>Glossaries<BR>
</CENTER>
</H2>
The terminology in the fields of learning disabilities and special education
can be baffling, at best! We've gathered these glossaries as handy references
to help you survive in the world of LD.<BR>
<H3>For Starters:</H3>
<MENU><A HREF="glossary_of_terms.html"><B>Learning Disabilities: Glossary
of Some Important Terms</B></A><B>, ERIC Digest #E517 - </B>A listing of
the definitions of terms commonly used in the field of learning disabilities.<BR>
<BR>
<B><A HREF="ld_glossary.html">Glossary of Learning Disabilities Terms</A>,
Understanding Learning Disabilities: A Parent Guide and Workbook, Learning
Disabilities Council, 1991</B> - A comprehensive guide to all terms used
in the field of learning disabilities.<BR>
<BR>
<B><A HREF="glossary_of_professionals.html">Glossary of Professionals </A>,
Parents' Educational Resource Center (PERC),<BR>
Parent Journal, Autumn 1996</B>- Useful listing of the professional who
may assist in meeting the needs of students with learning disabilities.
<BR>
<BR>
<B><A HREF="glossary_of_acronyms.html">The ABCs of Government, Special Education,
and Advocacy</A>, LDA bulletin -</B> A list of acronyms used in the fields
of special education, government and advocacy. <BR>
<BR>
</MENU>
<P>
