s, Ph.D.,  Their World 1992, National Center for Learning Disabilities </B>- A thought-  provoking article about the incredible impact teachers can have on children's  lives.  <P><A HREF="defining_self.html"><B>Defining the Self as a Learner for Children  with LD</B></A><B>, Augusta H. Gross, Ph.D., Their World 1996/1997, National  Center for Learning Disabilities</B> - This insightful article details  the critical importance of how children view themselves as learners. A  must-read for parents and teachers alike!  <P><A HREF="helplessness.html"><B>Learned Helplessness and Attribution  for Success and Failure in LD Students</B></A>, <B>Nicki G. Arnold, Their  World 1996/1997, National Center for Learning Disabilities</B> - This articles  explains the phenomenon of &quot;learned helplessness&quot; and offers  educational recommendations.</MENU><H3>Learn more about it:</H3><MENU>  <P><A HREF="../../finding_help/publications_help/social_pubs.html"><B>Our  selection of publications</B></A> on self- esteem provides more expert  advice.</MENU><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT SIZE="3" WIDTH="540%" NOSHADE><BR></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=-2>&copy;1996 WETA</FONT></BODY></HTML>
