ar.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="3" HSPACE="0"VSPACE="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></TD></TR><TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP"><TD><A HREF="../../audio_clips/audio-clips.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/audio.gif"ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Audio Clips" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="http://www.capaccess.org/cgi-bin/ldonline/netforum/ldf/a/1"><IMG SRC="../../images/bulletin.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0"VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Bulletin Board" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="../../ld_store/LD-Store.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/store.gif"ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="LD Store" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="http://www.weta.capaccess.org/ldonline/ld_survey.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/talk.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Talk Back" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="../../kidzone/kidzone.html"><IMG SRC="../../images/kid.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Kid Zone"NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><!-MENU Bar Ends Here> <BR><IMG SRC="../../images/bar.gif" ALIGN="TOP" WIDTH="540" HEIGHT="3" VSPACE="0"NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"><BR></P><H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Individualized Education Program</H2><P>Understanding the Individualized Education Program (I.E.P.) is essentialto maximizing special education services for students with learning disabilities.We've assembled informative articles plus useful forms to help parents andeducators make the most of the I.E.P. process.</P><H3><BR>For Starters:</H3><MENU>  <P><A HREF="../technology/at-iep.html"><B>Facts About Assistive Technology  and the IEP</B></A><B> </B>- This short list of considerations is helpful  when preparing the IEP for a student with learning disabilities.<BR>  <BR>  <B><A HREF="ieppub.html">Transition Services in the I.E.P.</A>, NICHCY  Publication, 1993 - </B>A complete guide to understanding the relationship  between transition planning and the I.E.P. process.<BR>  <BR>  <B><A HREF="whenyoumove.html">When You Move </A>, LDA Newsbriefs, July/August  1996 - </B>Be sure to understand what happens to a child's special education  program when moving to another state. This brief article contains important  information for parents.<BR>  <BR>  <B>Getting and Staying Organized: Parent Helpers - Understanding Learning  Disabilities: A Parent Guide and Workbook, Learning Disabilities Council,  1991 - </B>These helpful forms provide formats to <A HREF="report_organizer.html">organize  your child's reports</A> and <A HREF="phone_visit_log.html">track communication</A>  with school personnel and others.<BR>  <BR>  <B><A HREF="ld_teenagers_form.html">Involving Teens in the I.E.P.</A>,  Understanding Learning Disabilities: A Parent Guide and Workbook, Learning  Disabilities Council, 1991 </B>- These questionnaires are useful tools  for involving your teen or preteen in the I.E.P. process.</MENU><H3>Learn more about it:</H3><MENU>  <P><A HREF="../../finding_help/publications_help/ieps_legal_spec_ed_pubs.html"><B>Our  selected publications on IEPs, Legal Issues, and Special Education</B></A>  will help you gain more in-depth knowledge.</MENU><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT SIZE="3" WIDTH="540%" NOSHADE></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=-2>&copy;1996 WETA</FONT></BODY></HTML>
