"0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></TD></TR><TR ALIGN="LEFT" VALIGN="TOP"><TD><A HREF="../audio_clips/audio-clips.html"><IMG SRC="../images/audio.gif"ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Audio Clips" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="http://www.capaccess.org/cgi-bin/ldonline/netforum/ldf/a/1"><IMG SRC="../images/bulletin.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0"VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Bulletin Board" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="../ld_store/LD-Store.html"><IMG SRC="../images/store.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="LD Store"NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="http://www.weta.capaccess.org/ldonline/ld_survey.html"><IMG SRC="../images/talk.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0"BORDER="0" ALT="Talk Back" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD><TD><A HREF="kidzone.html"><IMG SRC="../images/kid.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="93" HEIGHT="20" HSPACE="0" VSPACE="0" BORDER="0" ALT="Kid Zone" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"></A></TD></TR></TABLE><BR><!-MENU Bar Ends Here> <BR><BR>Here's a list of some good books to help you handle your learning and attentionissues. Read up and good luck!<BR><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>NEW! Many Ways To Learn: Young People's Guide to LearningDisabilities</FONT></B> by Judith Stern and Uzi Ben-Ami</P><P>Written for children ages 8-14, this book tells what learning disabilitiesare and how a child can cope with school, friends and family members. Alsoavailable in a audiocassette.</P><P>Magination Press, 1996 - ISBN 0-945354-74-6 Phone: 212-242-6339</P><P><BR><HR ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="50%"></P><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>The School Survival Guide for Kids with LD</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+1> </FONT>by Cummings and Fisher<BR><BR>Tells kids with LD how to get organized; how to handle testing; tips fordoing better in reading, writing, spelling, and math; ways to keep schoolcool, and other tips<BR><BR>Free Spirit Publishing, 1991. ISBN 0-915793-32-6 Phone orders: 1-800-735-7323<BR></P><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="50%"><BR><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>The Survival Guide for Tenagers with LD</FONT></B> by Cummingsand Fisher<BR><BR>For ages 13 and up, a step-by-step handbook of school and life skills. Answersto questions about succeeding in school, and preparing for life as an adult<BR><BR>Free Spirit Publishing, 1991. ISBN 0-915793-51-2 Phone orders: 1-800-735-7323<BR><BR><BR><HR ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="50%"><BR><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>The Survival Guide for Kids with LD</FONT></B> by Cummingsand Fisher<BR><BR>Free Spirit Publishing, 1990. ISBN 0-915793-18-0 Phone orders: 1-800-735-7323<BR><BR><BR><HR ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="50%"><BR><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Keeping A Head in School</FONT> </B>by Mel Levine, M.D.<BR><BR>Aimed primarily at children ages 9 to 15, this book enhances motivationas it suggests specific ways to approch schoolwork, to bypass or overcomelearning disorders, and to manage the struggles that may beset studentsin school. Audio tape also available.<BR><BR>Educator's Publishing Service, 1990 - ISBN 0-8388-2069-7 Phone orders: 1-800-225-5750<BR><BR><HR ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="50%"></P><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>All Minds of Minds; A Young Student's Book about LearningAbilities and Learning Disorders</FONT> </B>by Mel Levine, M.D.<BR><BR>Written to help children in the elementary grades understand how they learn,how weaknesses make learning difficult, and how their strengths can be usedto improve their learning skills. As the title indicates, minds vary - noneis perfect - and everyone needs to learn to appreciate all kinds of minds.<BR>Also availabe on audio tape.<BR><BR>Educator's Publishing Service, 1993 - ISBN 0-8388-2095-0 - Phone orders:1-800-225-5750<BR><BR><HR ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="50%"><BR><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Learning to Slow Down and Pay Attention</FONT></B> by Dixonand Nadeau<BR><BR>Available from the ADD Warehouse at 1-800-233-9273</P><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT WIDTH="50%"><BR><BR><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Putting on the Brakes: Young People's Guide to UnderstandingAttention Deficit Hyperactivity Disorder</FONT> </B>by Quinn and Stern<BR><BR>Magination Press, 1991 - ISBN 0-945354-32-0 Phone: 212-242-6339<BR><BR><HR ALIGN=LEFT SIZE="3" WIDTH="540%" NOSHADE></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=-2>&copy;1996 WETA</FONT></BODY></HTML>
