 of 5 and 18 who has a learning disability. We must have your parent'spermission before we can use your work. Please enter as many pieces as youlike.<BR><BR><IMG SRC="../images/yellow.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="16" BORDER="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"><B>What We Are Looking For:</B> The weekly winnerswill be chosen on the basis of originality and creativity. We will alsoconsider the artist's or writer's age and grade.<BR><BR></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><B>INSTRUCTIONS</B></P><P><IMG SRC="../images/yellow.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="16" BORDER="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"><B>Please prepare your work according tothe following guidelines:<BR><BR><FONT COLOR="#663300" SIZE=+1><IMG SRC="../images/violet.gif" ALIGN="LEFT"WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="16" BORDER="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0">ARTWORK:<BR></FONT><FONT SIZE=+1>We would like to have your work on disk, if possible.</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+1>Otherwise, all artwork must be no larger than 9 inchesby 12 inches. Originals are preferred, but photographs are great too. Ifyour work is larger than 9 by 12 or you would like to send a sculpture orother 3D piece, please send us a photo. Remember to make a copy of it foryourself! <B>We will not be able to send back entries once they have beensubmitted.<BR><BR></B></FONT><B><FONT COLOR="#663300" SIZE=+1><IMG SRC="../images/violet.gif"ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="16" BORDER="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0">WRITING:</FONT><FONT SIZE=+1><BR>Please give us your work on disk, if possible. </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+1>Weaccept all kinds of written work. Send us stories, poetry, essays, or columns.The maximum length is 500 words (roughly two pages double spaced), but muchshorter pieces are also welcome. Once again, remember to make a copy foryourself, because we will not send back entries.<BR><BR><BR><IMG SRC="../images/yellow.gif" ALIGN="LEFT" WIDTH="16" HEIGHT="16" BORDER="0" NATURALSIZEFLAG="0"><B>To submit your work, print out this form, fillin the information below, and mail it with your work to:</B></FONT></P><BLOCKQUOTE>  <P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>LD OnLine<BR>  c/o WETA<BR>  P.O. Box 2626<BR>  Washington, D.C. 20013</FONT></B></P></BLOCKQUOTE><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Your last name, phone number, home address, and e-mailaddress are for our records only and will not appear on the Internet. Onlyyour first name, grade, and hometown may appear.</FONT></B></P><UL>  <LI><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Name: <INPUT NAME="STUDENT NAME" TYPE="text" SIZE=  "42"> </FONT></B>  <LI><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Grade: <INPUT NAME="GRADE" TYPE="text" SIZE="9"> Age:  </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+1><INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="6"></FONT>  <LI><B><FONT SIZE=+1>School:<INPUT NAME="SCHOOL" TYPE="text" SIZE="42">  </FONT></B>  <LI><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Phone: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+1><INPUT NAME="name"  TYPE="text" SIZE="30"></FONT>  <LI><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Home Address:<TEXTAREA NAME="ADDRESS" ROWS="4" COLS=  "32"  ></TEXTAREA> </FONT></B>  <LI><B><FONT SIZE=+1>E-Mail Address: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+1><INPUT NAME=  "name" TYPE="text" SIZE="30"><B> </B></FONT>  <LI><B><FONT SIZE=+1>Title of Piece Submitted: </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+1><INPUT  NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="42"><B> </B></FONT></UL><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1>If you like, enclose a picture of yourself and - ona separate sheet of paper - tell us a little about who you are ... interests,plans for the future ... anything you'd like to share. If your entry isaccepted, we will include this information on LD OnLine.<BR><BR>We must have your parent's permission to display your work; so please haveyour parent/guardian sign the Permission Slip below.<BR><BR></FONT></B></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=+1>LD OnLine<BR></FONT></B><FONT SIZE=+1>Permission Slip</FONT></P><P><FONT SIZE=+1>I agree that WETA, the creator of LD OnLine, may use thematerial I have created and submitted as part of its World Wide Web sitecreated for parents, children, teachers and other professionals interestedin learning disabilities. WETA will be free to use the material on LD OnLineand in any derivative works of LD OnLine, and to identify me as the authorof the material. WETA will have the right to reproduce, exhibit, distribute,and transmit LD OnLine (or authorize others to do so) worldwide in perpetuity.<BR><BR>I further consent to the use of my name and the material to promote LD OnLine,WETA, and public broadcasting as an institution in any medium.<BR><BR>I understand that I will not be paid for my participation.<BR><B><BR><BR>Student Signature </B><INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="30"><BR>Printed Name <INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="30"><BR>Address <INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="30"><BR>Date <INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="30"><BR><BR><BR>I represent that I am the parent/guardian of the above minor, and I agreethat this release is valid and enforceable.<BR><BR><B>Parent/Guardian Signature </B><INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="30"><BR>Printed Name <INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="30"><BR>Address <INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="30"><BR>Date <INPUT NAME="name" TYPE="text" SIZE="30"><BR></FONT></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=+1>THANK YOU FOR ENTERING YOUR ARTWORK ANDWRITING! GOOD LUCK!</FONT></B></P><P><B><FONT SIZE=+1><HR ALIGN=LEFT SIZE="3" WIDTH="540%" NOSHADE><BR></FONT></B></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><B><FONT SIZE=-2>&copy;1996 WETA</FONT></B></FORM></BODY><!--gform &amp;amp;quot;&amp;amp;lt;PRE&amp;amp;gt;\n=======================================================\n&amp;amp;quot;--><!--gform &amp;amp;quot;The date is: $(date) and the time is $(time)\n&amp;amp;quot;--><!--gform &amp;amp;quot;Form submitted by: $(student name)\n&amp;amp;quot;--><!-- A comment: Note use of environment variables just below --><!--gform &amp;amp;quot;He/She is using: $(HTTP_USER_AGENT)\n&amp;amp;quot;--><!--gform &amp;amp;quot;and their host is: $(REMOTE_HOST)\n&amp;amp;quot;--><!--gform &amp;amp;quot;Student name given is: $(student nam