<CENTER>    <IMG ALIGN="Left" SRC="../images/bobbrooks2.gif" WIDTH="130" HEIGHT="182">WETA    and Dr. Robert Brooks    <P>    Invite You  </CENTER></H2><H3>  <CENTER>    To Attend the Taping of  </CENTER></H3><H1>  <CENTER>    The Courage to Soar  </CENTER></H1><H3>  <CENTER>    A Television Program on Learning Disabilities<BR>    Produced by WETA, Washington, D.C.  </CENTER></H3><P><BR>Many children with learning disabilities feel isolated and dejected. Howcan we develop resilience in our kids? How can we give them the confidencethey will need to succeed? <B>Dr. Bob Brooks</B> shows parents and teachershow to find the "islands of competence" in every child and how to developnew areas of strength. He demonstrates how we can change the negative scriptswe often use with children and become more effective parents and teachers.<BR><BR><B>Dr. Robert Brooks</B> is a nationally-known learning disabilities expertand noted clinical psychologist whose stories deliver a message based onlove, encouragement, and resilience. <B>Dr. Brooks</B> teaches at HarvardMedical School and has worked with children with learning disabilities forover 25 years. <B>Dr. Brooks</B> lectures to business professionals, academicaudiences, parents, educators and mental health professionals throughoutthe United States. He is the author of the highly acclaimed book, <B>TheSelf-Esteem Teacher</B>. <BR><BR>Join <B>WETA</B> and <B>Dr. Brooks</B> on <B>Wednesday, November 20, 1996</B>for the taping of this new <B>WETA TV</B> program. Admission is free andyou may bring guests. But seating is limited, so <B>YOU MUST RESERVE YOURSEAT(S)</B> by calling <B>703-998-2692.</B><BR><BR>The taping will take place at the Alden Theatre located at the McLearn CommunityCenter, 1234 Ingleside Ave., McLean, VA. Parking is available. Please planto arrive between 6:30 p.m. and 6:50 p.m. so that we can have the entireaudience seated by 6:50. Because this is a taping for television, <B>we cannotadmit anyone after 6:50 p.m</B>. We will need everyone to remain in theauditorium for roughly three hours. We'll take a brief intermission duringthe taping session. We hope you can attend!<BR><P><CENTER>  Back to <A HREF="new.html">What's New</A></CENTER><P>  <HR SIZE="3" WIDTH="550%" ALIGN="LEFT" NOSHADE><BR><P><CENTER>  &copy;1996 WETA <BR>  <BR>  <BR>  <BR>  <BR></CENTER></BODY></HTML>
