yslexia: A Review of Medical Research&quot;  by Sylvia O. Richardson, M.D.  <LI>&quot;The Other Sixteen Hours: The Social and Emotional Problems of  Dyslexia&quot; by Michael Ryan, Ph.D.  <LI>&quot;Phonological Awareness: A Critical Factor in Dyslexia&quot; by  Joseph Torgesen, Ph.D.  <LI>&quot;Testing: Critical Components in the Identification of Dyslexia&quot;  by Jane Fell Greene, Ed.D. and Louisa Cook Moats, Ed.D.</UL><P><B>The Many Faces of Dyslexia</B>. Margaret Byrd Rawson, 1992. OrtonDyslexia Society. Ph. 410/296-0232</P><P><B>Dyslexia Across the Lifespan: A Fifty-Five Year Longitudinal Study</B>.Margaret Byrd Rawson, 1995. Orton Dyslexia Society. Ph. 410/296-0232</P><P><B>Intimacy with Language: A Forgotten Basic in Teacher Education</B>.Proceedings from the Orton Dyslexia Society's symposium &quot;Dyslexia andEvolving Educational Patterns,&quot;1988. Orton Dyslexia Society. Ph. 410/296-0232</P><P><B>All Language and the Creation of Literacy</B>. A selection of paperspresented at two symposia &quot;Whole Language and Phonics&quot; and &quot;Literacyand Language,&quot; 1991. Orton Dyslexia Society. Ph. 410/296-0232</P><P><B>Language and the Developing Child.</B> Katrina deHirsch. 1984. OrtonDyslexia Society. Ph. 410/296-0232</P><P><B>Reading, Writing, and Speech Problems in Children and Selected Papers</B>.Samuel T. Orton. A classic publication by the man who, more than any other,aroused the attention of the scientific community and provided the soundeducational principles on which much teaching of individuals with dyslexiatoday is based. Orton Dyslexia Society. Ph. 410/296-0232</P><P><B>Bridges to Reading</B>: what to do when your child has a reading problem.Parents' Educational Resource Center, 1995. ISBN 0964888890. Ph 800/471-9545<BR><BR><B>The Reading Brain</B>: the biological basis of dyslexia. Drake Duaneand David Gray, York Press, 1991. ISBN 0912751254<BR><BR><B>Overcoming Dyslexia in Children, Adolescents, and Adults</B>. Dale Jordon,PRO-Ed, 1989. ISBN 0890792046<BR><BR><B>Complete Reading Disabilities Handbook</B>: ready-to-use techniques forteaching reading to disabled students. Wilma Miller, The Center for AppliedResearch in Education, 1993. ISBN 0876282494<BR><BR><B>About Dyslexia:</B> unraveling the myth. Priscilla Vail, Modern LearningPress, 1990. ISBN 0935493344<BR><BR><B>Dyslexia &amp; Other Learning Disabilities</B>: the facts. Mark Selikowitz,Oxford University Press, 1993. ISBN 0192622994<BR><BR><B>Beginning to Read:</B> thinking and learning about print. M.J. Adams,The MIT Press, 1990. <BR></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><A HREF="pub_dist_list.html">Publishers &amp; DistributorsListing</A></P><P><HR ALIGN=LEFT SIZE="3" WIDTH="540%" NOSHADE><BR></P><P ALIGN=CENTER><FONT SIZE=-2>&copy;1996 WETA</FONT></BODY></HTML>
