acher Education</B>.Proceedings from the Orton Dyslexia Society's symposium &quot;Dyslexia andEvolving Educational Patterns,&quot;1988. Orton Dyslexia Society. Ph. 410/296-0232</P><P><B>All Language and the Creation of Literacy</B>. A selection of paperspresented at two symposia &quot;Whole Language and Phonics&quot; and &quot;Literacyand Language,&quot; 1991. Orton Dyslexia Society. Ph. 410/296-0232</P><P><B>Language and the Developing Child.</B> Katrina deHirsch. 1984. OrtonDyslexia Society. Ph. 410/296-0232</P><P><B>Reading, Writing, and Speech Problems in Children and Selected Papers</B>.Samuel T. Orton. A classic publication by the man who, more than any other,aroused the attention of the scientific community and provided the soundeducational principles on which much teaching of individuals with dyslexiatoday is based. Orton Dyslexia Society. Ph. 410/296-0232<BR><BR><B>Language-related Learning Disabilities: Their Nature and Treatment.</B>Adele Gerber, Paul H. Brookes Publishing Co., 1993. ISBN 1557660530<BR><BR><B>A Parent's Guide: Language and Behavioral Problems in Children</B>. SamGoldstein and Pam Hinerman, Neurology, Learning and Behavior Center, 1988.Hawthorne Educational Services. Ph. 800/542-1673<BR><BR><B>Childhood Speech, Language &amp; Listening Problems: What Every ParentShould Know.</B> Patricia Hamaguchi, Joh Wiley and Sons, 1995. ISBN 0471034134<BR><B><BR>The Early Identification of Language Impairment in Children</B>. James Law,ed., Chapman &amp; Hall, 1992. ISBN 1565930266<BR><BR><B>Language learning disabilities: A New and Practical Approach for Thosewho Work with Children and Families. </B>Sophie Lovinger, Mary Ellen Brandell,and Linda Seestedt, Continuum, 1991. ISBN 0824513223<BR><BR><B>Understanding Language Disorders: The Impact on Learning</B>. VivienneRatner and Laura Harris, Thinking Publications, 1994. ISBN 093059990x<BR><BR><B>Language Learning Disabilities in School-Age Children and Adolescents: